# Python Virtual Environment

Always use the project virtual environment at `.venv/` for running Python.

- Before running any `python` or `pip` command, ensure `.venv/` exists. If not, create it:
  ```
  python3.12 -m venv .venv
  ```
- Activate or reference the venv explicitly:
  - Use `.venv/bin/python` and `.venv/bin/pip` (macOS/Linux) or `.venv\Scripts\python` (Windows)
  - Or activate with `source .venv/bin/activate` before running commands
- Install the project in editable mode after creating the venv: `pip install -e .`
- Never install packages into the system Python
